{"questionId":"22644156","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Gundega claims that, on average, Latvian women are taller than Dutch women.</p>\n<p>Random samples of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> Latvian women and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> Dutch women are chosen, and their heights are measured.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/0fed9ec60607dcd5ba3d0ff6405cef575c6eac18.png\" width=\"580\" height=\"152\"></p>\n<p>Gundega performs a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>-test at the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math> significance level. It is assumed that the populations are normally distributed and have equal variances.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>less than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>160</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>160</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> <strong>OR</strong> labelled sketch of region <strong>OR</strong> calc syntax with correct bounds&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept either zero or a large negative value as the lower bound.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0447</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0447149</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>47</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22644156","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ2.4ai","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"less than 160 cm.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
